{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A key generator that uses the HMAC based HKDF algorithm to generate a new encryption key. SHA512 is used as the hash function."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The key generation consists of two phases: extraction and expansion."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"During the extraction a pseudo random key is generated from the input key material and an optional salt."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The expansion phase uses the pseudo random key and the info data block to derive the final key."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/SBSDKHKDFKeyGenerator\/init(inputKeyMaterial:info:salt:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/SBSDKHKDFKeyGenerator\/generateKey(keyLength:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods"}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKHKDFKeyGenerator"}],"modules":[{"name":"ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK"}],"platforms":[{"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"14.0"},{"name":"iPadOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"14.0"},{"name":"Mac Catalyst","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"14.0"}],"role":"symbol","title":"SBSDKHKDFKeyGenerator","externalID":"c:@M@ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK@objc(cs)SBSDKHKDFKeyGenerator","symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKHKDFKeyGenerator"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotbarcodescannersdk\/sbsdkhkdfkeygenerator"]},{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotbarcodescannersdk\